column5: I typically fish shallow and usually do excellent, but i am also usually here late June. So later July fishing might be part of it, most people here are fishing much deeper than i am used to. Weather has been pretty crappy too, more rain today.
Yep, Onaway. Love it here! Thanks for reply, will try along some weeds.
Edges as well inside weeds.weedless jigs definitely help.
Was real good,into a cold front now and getting lots of rain.Havnt been there for over a week
John is there still a burning ban?
Be up in VB 4 weeks from today.

Been fishing west side since Saturday, fishing is very very slow. At least it is for us, others in camp say they've been doing ok. Tried Scout Bay, Bay of Islands, McKenzie, Manitoba, Windigo, among other places so far
Sorry to hear that, trying to decide when during the year to plan our trip next year. Do you feel it's weather related? Time of the year? Just bad luck?

You guys are cruising around.Must be coming out of Fisherman's cove or Onaway.Havnt been to LS since last week and even then the fish we caught were not deep.Not sure how deep you guys are trying but might have to try different tactics/presentation.Find some weed beds we did well.
